Hi All,

Please resolve the below mentioned issue:

A soft phone with multiple endpoint support is used to make a loop back
call.
As per the attached captures, 
Consider ep1 calls ep2.
The response from the ep2 to INVITE includes RECORD-ROUTE header field
with originating pcscf and scscf and terminating scscf uris.
Terminating pcscf uri is not included.

And the ACK from ep1 is not forwarded by IMS Server to ep2 and hence 2xx
timeout happens and call is terminated.

Please find the logs of PCSCF, SCSCF and ICSCF and captures of call in
the attached zip file.

Please let us know what is the reason for not forwarding ACK.

Thanks in advance,

Regards,
Veena
